title: FOIL: Enrollment Projection Source Data including Live Birth Data and Communications (Locust Valley Central School District)

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: FOIL: Enrollment Projection Source Data including Live Birth Data and Communications (Locust Valley Central School District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Live Birth Data including constant birth rate, long term, short term and average birth rates for within the district for current and previous 6 years.

Birth to Kindergarten Survival Ratio used for the past 10 years by year.

Projected Kindergarten Enrollment for the past 10 years by year, and supporting data.

Any communications with NYS DOH or County DOH or other data service provider requesting, receiving or inquiring regarding live birth data, birth to kindergarten survival rate or other statistical data used for projecting enrollment.

Copies of all enrollment projections for the past 6 years and source statistical data, including but not limited to live birth data which were used to provide projected enrollment data upon which securities purchasers rely.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing in response to your determination on April 11, 2023, stating that the Locust Valley Central School District does not maintain or possess the records I requested in my Freedom of Information Law (FOIL) request dated March 5, 2023.

Based on the disclosure documents published on the Municipal Securities Rulemaking Board's Electronic Municipal Market Access (EMMA) website, it appears that the District does, in fact, produce enrollment projections and attests to these projections in multiple instances. Specifically, on page A-2 (page 20 in the PDF) of the document found at the following link: https://emma.msrb.org/P11520405.pdf

Given this information, I kindly request that you reconsider and reevaluate my original FOIL request for the following records:

1. Live Birth Data including constant birth rate, long term, short term, and average birth rates for within the district for the current and previous six years.
2. Birth to Kindergarten Survival Ratio used for the past ten years by year.
3. Projected Kindergarten Enrollment for the past ten years by year, and supporting data.
4. Any communications with NYS DOH or County DOH or other data service provider requesting, receiving, or inquiring regarding live birth data, birth to kindergarten survival rate, or other statistical data used for projecting enrollment.
5. Copies of all enrollment projections for the past six years and source statistical data, including but not limited to live birth data which were used to provide projected enrollment data upon which securities purchasers rely.

If the District does not maintain these specific records, I kindly request that you provide any alternative records or information that may help fulfill my request, such as the departments or agencies that might maintain such records.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Bellevue School District – Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including District Responses for the years 2015 - 2021
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act [RCW 42.56] I hereby request the following records:

I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District and a complete electronic copy of the District's Responses to these Public Records Requests for the time period January 1, 2010 through November 4, 2021.

In the event the District chooses to provide these records in installments over time I request the records to be produced in reverse chronological order - from the most recent records to the earliest.

If this request is denied in whole or part, I ask that you justify all deletions by reference to specific exemptions of the PRA. I also request a detailed contemporaneous log to be provided for any document withheld or redacted.

For each responsive record the District contends is exempt from public disclosure, in whole or in part, please specifically identify the record by subject, title, author, custodian and date, and state how a specific statutory exemption applies to each record as required by RCW 42.56.210(3) and Rental Housing Ass'n v. Des Moines, 165 Wn.2d 525, 199 P.3d 393 (2009).

I request electronic production of all electronic records in the original NATIVE electronic format for each record. 

I request for these public records to be produced by public (no password) e-mail attachment or link. If electronic attachment or link is not possible, an alternative would be to produce responsive records via USB DRIVE or DATA CD-ROM.

THIS REQUEST IS NOT BEING MADE FOR COMMERCIAL PURPOSES.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

PRA Audit

communications.subject: RE: Washington Public Records Act Request: Bellevue School District – Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including District Responses for the years 2015 - 2021
communications.communication:
PRR 11032021-Anon
Dear Requestor:
Please include in the above request number in all of your correspondence with this office.
Your request is:

I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District and a complete electronic copy of the District's Responses to these Public Records Requests for the time period January 1, 2010 through November 4, 2021.
Thank you for making your July 7 status inquiry, which will inform the District’s next installment to your request, presently estimated for July 20, 2022.
We may have a misunderstanding as to what records you intend to request. I have been producing, on behalf of the District, public records request logs, which are “electronic cop[ies]” of “Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District.” I understood the logs to be directly responsive to the first part of your request.

Clarification Questions

  1.  If you do not believe public records request logs are responsive to your request, please clarify your request to explain what records you intended to request by seeking “a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District.”
  2.  As you likely know, Washington law does not require agencies to retain records relating to public requests records beyond two years after the request is closed. The Local Government Common Records Retention Schedule, section 5.4, sets forth records that may be destroyed after two years, which “[i]ncludes but is not limited to:”

“Internal and external correspondence relating to the request;”

“Records documenting the public records provided to the requestor (copies or lists of the records provided, etc.);” and

“Records documenting the public records (or portions) withheld (exemption logs, copies of portions redacted, etc.).”

Thus, many such records relating to requests closed more than 2 years prior to the date of your request no longer exist. That is also why I was producing request logs to you. For many of the older requests, the request logs may be the only existing records. Do you no longer want to receive request logs, even if they may be the only existing records potentially responsive to your request with respect to requests closed more than two years prior to the date of your request?

  1.  I was also producing request logs to give you an opportunity to identify particular requests that were of interest to you, so searches for records relating to those requests could be prioritized. Is that an opportunity that is of interest to you?

Your answers to these clarification questions are due within 30 days, that is, on or before August 12. The timing of your answers will affect the timing of the District’s next response. The District will not proceed with the next installment scheduled for July 20, pending receipt of your answers, so that the District’s responses can reflect an accurate understanding of what you are requesting. If you do not answer within 30 days, your request may be closed.

The District is under no obligation to produce records to you in a reverse chronological order. Records will be produced in a manner that reflects the most efficient method of assembling and reviewing potentially responsive records.

I look forward to hearing from you.
Best regards,

Helen A. Boyer
Public Records Officer
Bellevue School District No. 405

communications.subject: RE: Washington Public Records Act Request #11032021-Anon
communications.communication:
ANSWERS TO YOUR QUESTIONS:

Clarification Questions

1. If you do not believe public records request logs are responsive to your request, please clarify your request to explain what records you intended to request by seeking “a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District.”

ANSWER: 

PRODUCE A COPY (NATIVE ELECTRONIC FORMAT PREFERRED) OF ALL PUBLIC RECORDS REQUESTS RECEIVED BY THE BELLEVUE SCHOOL DISTRICT FOR THE TIME PERIOD JANUARY 1, 2010 THROUGH NOVEMBER 4, 2021.

PRODUCE A COPY (NATIVE ELECTRONIC FORMAT PREFERRED) OF EACH RESPONSE TO ALL PUBLIC RECORDS REQUESTS RECEIVED BY THE BELLEVUE SCHOOL DISTRICT FOR THE TIME PERIOD JANUARY 1, 2010 THROUGH NOVEMBER 4, 2021.

2. As you likely know, Washington law does not require agencies to retain records relating to public requests records beyond two years after the request is closed. The Local Government Common Records Retention Schedule, section 5.4, sets forth records that may be destroyed after two years, which “[i]ncludes but is not limited to:”

“Internal and external correspondence relating to the request;”

“Records documenting the public records provided to the requestor (copies or lists of the records provided, etc.);” and

“Records documenting the public records (or portions) withheld (exemption logs, copies of portions redacted, etc.).”

Thus, many such records relating to requests closed more than 2 years prior to the date of your request no longer exist. That is also why I was producing request logs to you. For many of the older requests, the request logs may be the only existing records. Do you no longer want to receive request logs, even if they may be the only existing records potentially responsive to your request with respect to requests closed more than two years prior to the date of your request?

1. I was also producing request logs to give you an opportunity to identify particular requests that were of interest to you, so searches for records relating to those requests could be prioritized. Is that an opportunity that is of interest to you?

ANSWER: 

REQUEST THAT YOU WORK AS DIRECTED AND PRODUCE ALL RESPONSIVE RECORDS REQUESTED. 
THE LOGS ARE RESPONSIVE RECORDS AND SHOULD BE PRODUCED. 
ALL PUBLIC RECORDS REQUESTS AND RESPONSES RETAINED BY THE DISTRICT SHOULD BE PRODUCED.
 A COMPLETE SEARCH FOR ALL RESPONSIVE RECORDS SHOULD HAVE ALREADY BEEN CONDUCTED BY THE DISTRICT.
AT A MINIMUM ALL RECORDS FROM 2020 AND 2021 SHOULD HAVE ALREADY BEEN PRODUCED IN REVERSE CHRONOLOGICAL FORMAT.

QUESTION: HAS THE DISTRICT CONDUCTED A COMPLETE SEARCH FOR ALL RESPONSIVE RECORDS REQUESTED INCLUDING INCLUDE A SEARCH OF ALL COMPUTERS AND DIGITAL STORAGE DEVICES OWNED, OPERATED, OR CONTROLLED BY DISTRICT EMPLOYEES?

IF SO, PLEASE LIST ALL LOCATIONS SEARCHED BY THE DISTRICT IN DETAIL. 

PLEASE DISCONTINUE ANY AND ALL PERSONAL SOLICITATIONS AND PERSONAL INQUIRIES INCLUDING YOUR MOST RECENT REGARDING PROVIDING UNSOLICITED OPPORTUNITIES OF INTEREST.

Thank you.

PRR 11032021-Anon-Muckrock
Dear Requestor:
On behalf of the Bellevue School District, I am making a fourth installment to your request as follows:

I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the Bellevue School District and a complete electronic copy of the District's Responses to these Public Records Requests for the time period January 1, 2010 through November 4, 2021.
You indicated in your July 14, 2022 response to clarifying questions below that you agree that public record request logs are responsive to your request. Therefore, appended hereto please find:

2019 Log

This record contains information that is exempt under the Public Records Act, Chapter 42.56.RCW. Redactions made pursuant to the Act are marked with an overlying code. I have also attached a Redaction and Exemption Codes chart that provides an explanation of the basis for the exemptions applied. If no code is applied or if a code is partially visible, the applicable codes are 1A, 10A.

I regret that it was not possible to make an installment of records to you on the previously estimated date of August 3, 2022. The factors affecting the extension of that date included staff absences due to illness and vacation break, and ongoing workload in this department.
As I indicated to you in response to your request PRR 11022021-Anon, the District is not withholding any records from you and has nothing to hide.
Please direct all messages pertaining to your request to the public records mailbox, publicrecords@bsd405.org<mailto:publicrecords@bsd405.org>.
The automated correspondence features of the Muckrock site are not an efficient way to correspond or to review correspondence. Please do not interrupt our correspondence history by cutting messages out of the email string, or by excerpting them in any way. I know that the correspondence history can get long. However, it is important in order for us to communicate effectively that a complete and accurate history of our communications is readily available to both of us.
I estimate a next installment to your request will be made on or before September 26, 2022. Estimated dates are subject to change. The timing of this estimate is based on anticipated staff absences, operational responsibilities related to school reopening, and the workload in this department.
Best regards,

Helen A. Boyer

title: Masked LEOs (Metropolitan Police Department)

communications.subject: DC Freedom of Information Act Request: Masked LEOs (Metropolitan Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the DC Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Policies, including implementation, termination and expiration notices, mentioning or discussing mask mandates or requirements for employees.

2. Reports regarding alleged violations of or non-compliance with mask mandates or requirements.

3. Records documenting any disciplinary actions taken regarding Item #2.

4. Emails, letters, memos and other written or memorialized discussions with unions or employee representatives regarding actual or proposed mask mandates or requirements (such as those requested in Item #1).

I am a member of the news media and request classification as such. I have previously written about the government and its activities, with some reaching over 100,000 readers in outlets such as Gizmodo, MuckRock, Motherboard, Property of the People, Unicorn Riot, and The Outline, among others. As such, as I have a reasonable expectation of publication and my editorial and writing skills are well established. In addition, I discuss and comment on the files online and make them available through non-profits such as the library Internet Archive and the journalist non-profit MuckRock, disseminating them to a large audience. While my research is not limited to this, a great deal of it, including this, focuses on the activities and attitudes of the government itself. As such, it is not necessary for me to demonstrate the relevance of this particular subject in advance.

As my primary purpose is to inform about government activities by reporting on it and making the raw data available, I request that fees be waived.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emma North-Best

communications.subject: Acknowledgement Letter 2021-FOIA-08043
communications.communication: DearMs./Mrs. North-Best, TheFreedom of Information Act (FOIA) requires that requests describe the recordssought with sufficient detail to allow an agency employee familiar with thesubject area of the request to locate the records with a reasonable amount ofeffort.  More specifically, 1 DCMR § 402.4 states that: A request shallreasonably describe the desired record(s). Please provide a timeframe for therecords you are seeking. Yourrequest does not adequately describe the records sought; therefore, we areunable to process it at this time.  If you wish to pursue your request, pleaseprovide a timeframe for the records you areseeking to enable our office to process your request. If we do not receive the clarificationrequired within five (5) business days from the date of thisletter, we will presume that you are no longer interested in pursuing yourrequest and consider this a constructive withdrawal and close our file. In the meantime, your request will be placed on hold and the time for ourresponse will not accrue under 1 DMCR § 405.6. Regards, LatrinaCrumlin StaffAssistant, FOIA MetropolitanPolice Department 300Indiana Avenue, Rm 4153 Washington,DC  20001

title: Maine State Employees (2018 - 2022)

communications.subject: Maine Freedom of Access Act Request: Maine State Employees (2018 - 2022)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maine Freedom of Access Act, I hereby request the following records:

Monthly electronic listings of all employees of the Maine Executive Branch from January 1, 2018 to July 31, 2022. Specifically, I am seeking electronic listings of all individuals employed within all state agencies, commissions, and departments for each month from January 1, 2018 to July 31, 2022.

For each month, I’m seeking a spreadsheet, database, or delimited text file(s) — not paper records or a PDF created from data — with the following fields for each employee: full legal name, unique employee identification code, date of birth or age, title, department or agency, race, gender, full-time/part-time status, location, hire date, termination date, civil service status, and gross annual salary. If you cannot produce any of these fields, please let me know and generate only the available variables.

If these data are not available at monthly intervals, please produce the datasets at the most frequent interval possible. For example, if the data is not available monthly, please produce the data at quarterly intervals.

In addition, please include any lookup tables that may be needed to interpret the data. For example, if departments are listed with codes linked to a separate table, I will be happy to join the records myself, rather than require your staff to do so.

I am comfortable working with large data sets and can receive the records in a variety of formats (.dbf, .csv, .mdb, etc).

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as we believe this request is in the public interest, as suggested but not stipulated by 1 M.R.S.A. § 408(6). The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Goehring

We may also require the payment of costs as authorized by law.

DAFS will notify you, within a reasonable time, of a date and time for review and copying of the documents (or by transmitting copies to you) not protected from disclosure.  Should any of the requested documents be withheld, we will identify the reason for not disclosing them.

communications.subject: eFOIA Request Received
communications.communication:
# Individual Information

Prefix First Name Middle Name Last Name Suffix Email Phone Location

# Domestic Address

Address Line 1 Address Line 2 City State Postal

# Agreement to Pay

How you will pay

I am requesting a fee waiver for my request and have reviewed the FOIA
reference guide. If my fee waiver is denied, I would like to limit my request
to the two free hours of searching and 100 duplicated pages.

# Proof Of Affiliation for Fee Waiver

Waiver Explanation

    
    
    I am a member of the news media and request classification as such. I have
    previously
    written about the government and its activities, with some reaching over
    100,000
    readers in outlets such as Gizmodo, MuckRock, Motherboard, Property of the
    People,
    Unicorn Riot, and The Outline, among others. As such, as I have a reasonable
    expectation of publication and my editorial and writing skills are well
    established. In
    addition, I discuss and comment on the files online and make them available
    through
    non-profits such as the library Internet Archive and the journalist
    non-profit MuckRock,
    disseminating them to a large audience. While my research is not limited to
    this, a great
    deal of it, including this, focuses on the activities and attitudes of the
    government itself.
    As such, it is not necessary for me to demonstrate the relevance of this
    particular
    subject in advance.
    Further, case law states that “proof of the ability to disseminate the
    released information
    to a broad cross- section of the public is not required.” Judicial Watch,
    Inc. v. Dep’t of
    Justice, 365 F.3d 1108, 1126 (D.C. Cir. 2004); see Carney v. U.S. Dep’t of
    Justice, 19 F.
    3d 807, 814-15 (2d Cir. 1994). Further, courts have held that "qualified
    because it also
    had “firm” plans to “publish a number of . . . ‘document sets’” concerning
    United States
    foreign and national security policy." Under this criteria, as well, I
    qualify as a member of
    the news media.
    Additionally, courts have held that the news media status "focuses on the
    nature of the
    requester, not its request. The provision requires that the request be “made
    by” a
    representative of the news media. Id. § 552(a)(4)(A)(ii)(II). A newspaper
    reporter, for
    example, is a representative of the news media regardless of how much
    interest there is
    in the story for which he or she is requesting information." As such, the
    details of the
    request itself are moot for the purposes of determining the appropriate fee
    category.
    As my primary purpose is to inform about government activities by reporting
    on it and
    making the raw data available, I request that fees be waived.

Documentation Files

# Non-Individual FOIA Request

Request Information

    
    
    To Whom It May Concern:
    
    Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following
    records:
    
    Copies of file numbers:
    
    * 62-46855
    * 62-116659
    * 75-238
    * 100-151646
    * 100-391697
    * 100-445578
    * 140-26813
    * 161-9153
    
    The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and
    this request is not being made for commercial purposes.
    
    In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me
    of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the
    request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM
    if not.
    
    Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look
    forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days,
    as the statute requires.
    
    Sincerely,
    
    Emma Best
    
    Attachments:
    
    
    https://cdn.muckrock.com/outbound_composer_attachments/EmmaBest/74619/Fee20category20and20search20parameters.pdf
    Upload documents directly:
    https://https://www.muckrock.comhttps://accounts.muckrock.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.muckrock.com%2Faccounts%2Flogin%2F%3Fnext%3D%252Faccounts%252Fagency_login%252Ffederal-bureau-of-investigation-10%252Fnathan-glazer-refs-79670%252F%253Femail%253Defoia%252540subscriptions.fbi.gov&url_auth_token=AAAj2ProGzquHYFeb-SMkiAXsEc%3A1i3Bwl%3AZsRaiZTHkmVOyzg668DpbKoiMn8

** 

Please be advised that efoia@subscriptions.fbi.gov is a no-reply email
address. Questions regarding your FOIA request may be directed to
foipaquestions@fbi.gov. If you have received a FOIPA request number, please
include this in all correspondence concerning your request. Please note eFOIPA
requests are processed in the order that they are received. If you have not
received a FOIPA request number, your request is in the process of being
opened at which time it will be assigned a FOIPA request number and
correspondence will be forthcoming.

** 

Upon receipt of your FOIPA request number, you may check the status of your
FOIPA request on the FBI’s electronic FOIA Library (The Vault) on the FBI’s
public website, http://vault.fbi.gov by clicking on the ‘Check Status of Your
FOI/PA Request tool’ link. Status updates are performed on a weekly basis. If
you receive a comment that your FOIPA request number was not located in the
database, please check back at a later date.

title: Police Staff Roster (April 2023) (Lake Forest Police Park Department)

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Police Staff Roster (April 2023) (Lake Forest Police Park Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Staff roster including but not limited to first and last names, job titles, areas of assignment, and badge, serial, and other identifying numbers. In order of preference, I would prefer that this data be provided as: plain text with comma-separated-values (i.e., a "CSV" file), OpenDocument spreadsheet, Excel spreadsheet, or the native electronic format of the software from which this information is retrieved in fulfillment of my request. I specifically request that you not create a new record for me by rendering to PDF or by printing your electronic record then scanning it to make a series of images of the printed data.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

title: Duanesburg Central School Superintendent's Conference Days

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Duanesburg Central School Superintendent's Conference Days
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide the following:

-A copy of any and all the information pertaining to the four (4) Duanesburg Superintendent's Conference Days on September 6, 2022, on October 7, 2022, on January 27, 2023, and on March 17, 2023.
-A copy of any and all handouts provided by the Duanesburg Superintendent to school staff during the Duanesburg Superintendent's Conference Days on September 6, 2022, on October 7, 2022, on January 27, 2023, and on March 17, 2023.
-A copy of any and all handouts provided by any and all guests who attended the Duanesburg Superintendent's Conference Days on September 6, 2022, on October 7, 2022, on January 27, 2023, and on March 17, 2023.
-A copy of any and all official emails received and sent by the Duanesburg Superintendent to school staff and school guests pertaining to the Duanesburg Superintendent's Conference Days on September 6, 2022, on October 7, 2022, on January 27, 2023, and on March 17, 2023.
-A copy of any and all digital information used by the Duanesburg Superintendent during the Duanesburg Superintendent's Conference Days on September 6, 2022, on October 7, 2022, on January 27, 2023, and on March 17, 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Clifford Bradshaw

communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request #R000407-020223
communications.communication:
Dear Records Access Officer:

This is an appeal of the Office of the Governor’s determination on 4/4/23, regarding the above request. The Office of the Governor has constructively denied my request. The possible return date of 5/1/23 — nearly 3 months after the request was filed – is unreasonable, given the narrow scope of the request.

Because of this appeal, the Office of the Governor is required by law to provide specific reasons within 10 business days explaining why this request cannot be filled, or else, must provide the records sought.

According to the Committee on Open Government, if a government entity acknowledges that a request has been received, but has failed to grant access by the specific date given beyond twenty business days, or if the specific date given is unreasonable, a request may be considered to have been constructively denied (see §89[4][a]).  In such a circumstance, the denial may be appealed in accordance with §89(4)(a), which states in relevant part that:

“...any person denied access to a record may within thirty days appeal in writing such denial to the head, chief executive or governing body of the entity, or the person therefore designated by such head, chief executive, or governing body, who shall within ten business days of the receipt of such appeal fully explain in writing to the person requesting the record the reasons for further denial, or provide access to the record sought.” 

I, on behalf of New York Focus, am requesting either you fill this FOIL request, or else provide a full explanation as to the reason for the denial, as required by law, of this public record.

Sincerely,
Sam Mellins
Senior Reporter, New York Focus

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: ESPLER
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All threat assessments, field reports, intelligence updates, emails, and email attachments, which mention the following terms or names:

- Erotic Service Providers Union (ESPU)
- Erotic Service Providers Legal Education and Research Project (ESPLER or ESPLERP)
- Maxine Doogan
- Kristin DiAngelo
- Starchild

This request has a date range of 1/1/2013 until the date this request is processed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tara Burns

communications.communication:
VIA EMAIL: DSHSPublicDisclosure@dshs.wa.gov

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

A COMPLETE COPY OF THE PERSONAL STORAGE TABLE FILE (.PST FILE) FOR THE EMAIL ACCOUNT: 

traci.yerbich@dshs.wa.gov

For the time period: 01-01-2022 to 10-28-2023.

Upon information and belief “traci.yerbich@dshs.wa.gov” is the email account currently assigned to Washington State Department of Social and Health Services - Claims Officer - Division of Child Support - Attorney at Law - Traci Annette Yerbich, DOB: 8-16-1968, Address: 3906 60th Street Ct NW Gig Harbor, WA 98335.
FORMAT OF PRODUCTION OF RESPONSIVE RECORDS

Please provide the requested .pst file in the NATIVE electronic format as stored on agency email servers. 

If the .pst file cannot be produced in the NATIVE .pst format, explain in exact technical and procedural detail under the Washington State Public Records Act (RCW 42.56) WHY the file cannot be produced as the .pst file is electronically and NATIVELY stored.

COMMUNICATIONS – NO 3rd PARTY PORTAL TO BE USED

Washington State Law is clear that the use of 3rd party “portals” for a public records request is optional for the requestor. Respectfully I decline. Please provide all records electronically via direct email attachment or internet download link with no password protection and no 3rd party registration.

NO 3RD PARTY COMMUNICATION OBLIGATION

Do not direct me to use, register for, or communicate with your agency via any 3rd party company portal including but not limited to FOIA Online, GovQA, Next Request, FOIA Express, Just FOIA FOIA Direct, Web Form, or any other online portal. Use direct email for all communications.

If you provide a web-based link to publish responsive records, please make the records completely public without any login, registration, sign-in, or any other end-user restriction.

EXEMPTION LOGS

Please ensure any redactions or exemptions claimed in the production of responsive records are accompanied by a complete and detailed exemption log noting the valid legal reason for each exemption at each redaction location in the record as well as the specific number of pages, if any, that your agency redacts or withholds in their entirety. Every redaction must be keyed by footnote or by other clear reference to the specific justification for that redaction, and only the minimal exempt portion of any record may be withheld.

FEES

In the event that there are fees, please inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request in strict compliance with all provisions of the Washington State Public Records Act.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

communications.subject: RE: Washington Public Records Act Request: Traci Annette Yerbich - Claims Officer - Division of Child Support - Attorney at Law - Washington State Department of Social and Health Services
communications.communication:
NOVEMBER 8, 2022

VIA EMAIL: DSHSPublicDisclosure@dshs.wa.gov

“November 7, 2022

MuckRock News
Dept MR 135902
263 Hunington Ave
Boston MA 02115

Emailed to: 135902-99478262@requests.muckrock.com

RE: Request for Public Records – DSHS Request ID # 202210 PRR 469

This letter responds to your request under the Public Records Act, Ch. 42.56 RCW. We received
your request on October 31, 2022. Please use the above request ID number when contacting us
about this request.

You asked for a copy of the Personal Storage Table (.pst) file for Traci Yerbich, email account
traci.yerbich@dshs.wa.gov for the time period January 1, 2022 – October 28, 2023 in Native
Format.

Please note, we understand this request includes records created on or before October 31, 2022 (date
request was received) and does not include records that may be created in the future. Under RCW
42.56.080(1), a public records request must be for an existing identifiable record. Requests cannot
be “standing” requests for records that may be available in the future (Sargent v. Seattle Police
Dept. 2011). If you wish to receive records related to the above subjects that may be created during
the next year (November 1, 2022 – October 28, 2023), you will need to make a new request at a
future date.

You have asked to receive records in native .pst format. We will make every effort to comply with
this request when native format is available. Please note, if records require the redaction of exempt
information we only have the ability to provide them in PDF format. Please note: emails in the .pst
file may contain the following:

Records that include/contain individual DSHS Client information will be redacted and/or
withheld as those records would be confidential and privileged under RCW 74.04.060, and
other state and federal laws that govern DSHS programs. Records related to DCS are also
private and confidential under RCW 26.23.120. We must have a valid authorization or
court order to allow us to give you client records held by DSHS.

Responsive records may include thousands of all-staff emails, meeting notices, calendar
appointments, distribution list emails with multiple recipients, and other emails received by this
employee during the course of their normal job duties. Additionally, responsive records may also
include thousands of emails that contain large spreadsheets/lists of employees or clients that will
require extensive review and, when converted for review for potential redactions, each spreadsheet
may be hundreds of pages in length. Do you wish to receive these types of records?

If we do not receive clarification from you within two weeks, or by November 21, 2022, we will
understand you are seeking the records noted above and will process your request accordingly.
Records located in response to your request will likely include lists of individuals. RCW
42.56.070(8) prohibits agencies from providing access to lists of individuals when requested for a
commercial purpose. If you wish to receive lists of individuals, we require completion of the
enclosed declaration form certifying that you are not making this public records request for
commercial purposes. Without completion of this form lists of individuals will be redacted or
withheld under RCW 42.56.070(8).

We will send your request to the DSHS programs that may hold responsive records. Due to current
workloads, the number of other pending requests and the scope of your request, we estimate it will
take up to 45 business days or until about January 13, 2023, to find, review, copy and produce any
available records from Department programs. Records will be provided in installments as
appropriate.

We will contact you when we find records and tell you of any charges under RCW 42.56.120 and
WAC 388-01-080. DSHS may charge for copies of electronic records, actual cost of other copies
and postage. If there is a charge, we will send you the records after receiving a check made out to
DSHS for the amount due.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact our office or Norah West at
norah.west@dshs.wa.gov.

Sincerely,
Andrea Sterzer
DSHS Public Records Specialist
Phone: 360-902-8484/Fax: 360-902-7855 / DSHSPublicDisclosure@dshs.wa.gov
Enclosure
Cc: Norah West”

RESPONSE:

RE: Letter dated November 7, 2022

RECORDS REQUESTED IN NATIVE .PST FORMAT

You stated “Please note, if records require the redaction of exempt information, we only have the ability to provide them in PDF format.”

This is not a factual statement. It has been confirmed that DSHS utilizes standard office software in the course of regular business operations capable of exporting .pst files to .pdf format, applying redactions were appropriate and/or allowed by law, and then re-importing the redacted files back to the original .pst format for production.

This request is for a specifically identified record, the Personal Storage Table (.pst) file for Traci Yerbich, email account traci.yerbich@dshs.wa.gov for the time period January 1, 2022 – October 28, 2023 in Native .pst format.

The burden, and/or legal responsibility for the application of any redactions or exemptions allowed by statute is the sole obligation of your Agency, not this requestor. 

The public record, which has been properly identified is what needs to be produced.

NO COMMERICAL PURPOSE - DECLARATION

This public records request is not specifically seeking a list of individuals or a list of any kind. We understand that contained in the requested .pst file identified lists may in fact be captured for production as generated and utilized in the regular course of business by your agency. 

DECLARATION: I declare this public records request does not seek any list of individuals nor does it seek any specific list of any kind and the request itself is not for profit in any way.

This declaration of no commercial purpose satisfies the requirements of RCW 42.56.070(8).

You state: “Responsive records may include thousands of all-staff emails, meeting notices, calendar appointments, distribution list emails with multiple recipients, and other emails received by this employee during the course of their normal job duties. Additionally, responsive records may also include thousands of emails that contain large spreadsheets/lists of employees or clients that will MuckRock News 202210 PRR 469 November 7, 2022 Page 2 require extensive review and, when converted for review for potential redactions, each spreadsheet may be hundreds of pages in length. Do you wish to receive these types of records?”

This request is for a specifically identified record, the Personal Storage Table (.pst) file for Traci Yerbich, email account traci.yerbich@dshs.wa.gov for the time period January 1, 2022 – October 28, 2023 in Native .pst format. We wish to receive this identified public record.

You state: “Records located in response to your request will likely include lists of individuals.”

Provide proof of the accuracy of this statement.

In any event, this request is not for profit in any way. The no commercial purpose declaration has ben satisfied as per RCW 42.56.070(8).

RECORDS INSTALLMENTS

If records are to be provided in installments, please provide installments of records in reverse chronological order with the newest dated records produced first and the oldest records being produced last.

Thank you.

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Live Birth Data including constant birth rate, long term, short term and average birth rates for within the district for current and previous 6 years.

Birth to Kindergarten Survival Ratio used for the past 10 years by year.

Projected Kindergarten Enrollment for the past 10 years by year, and supporting data.

Any communications with NYS DOH or County DOH or other data service provider requesting, receiving or inquiring regarding live birth data, birth to kindergarten survival rate or other statistical data used for projecting enrollment.

Copies of all enrollment projections for the past 6 years and source statistical data, including but not limited to live birth data which were used to provide projected enrollment data upon which securities purchasers rely.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

title: VANCOUVER PUBLIC SCHOOLS DISTRICT – (2019) Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including the District Responses for the year 2019 – and 6,681 recently located electronic pages.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: VANCOUVER PUBLIC SCHOOLS DISTRICT – (2019) Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including the District Responses for the year 2019 – and 6,681 recently locate
communications.communication:
VANCOUVER PUBLIC SCHOOLS DISTRICT – (2019) Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including the District Responses for the year 2019 – and 6,681 recently located electronic pages.

Via email: publicrecordsrequest@vansd.org

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act [RCW 42.56] I hereby request the following records:

1.	I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by your agency in the year 2019 and a complete electronic copy of your agency's Responses to each of these Public Records Requests for the year 2019.

2.	Upon information and belief your agency has recently scanned into electronic format 5,377 pages of documents responsive to this request.

3.	Upon information and belief your agency possesses another 1304 electronic pages of documents responsive to this request for a total of 6,681 electronic pages responsive to this request , please provide these electronic  records.

Note: Parents and students seeking GRADES and/or TRANSRIPTS in the year 2019 can be excluded from this request.

PRODUCTION AND DELIVERY OF ELECTRONIC RECORDS

The use of 3rd party “portals” (Such as GOVQA or NEXTREQUEST) for communication and production of records in response to a public records request is optional for the requestor in the State of Washington. Respectfully we decline to use any 3rd party "portal" system, specifically GOVQA and NEXTREQUEST. Please provide all records electronically via direct email attachment, or via no password, no registration internet cloud-based download link.
Please do not direct or invite us to use, register for, or communicate with your agency via any 3rd party portal including but not limited to FOIAOnline, GovQA, NextRequest, FOIAExpress, JustFOIA FOIADirect, WebForm, or any other commercial 3rd party records portal service.
RCW 42.56.080 - Identifiable records—Facilities for copying—Availability of public records.

"...Agencies shall honor requests received in person during an agency's normal office hours, or by mail or email, for identifiable public records unless exempted by provisions of this chapter. No official format is required for making a records request; however, agencies may recommend that requestors submit requests using an agency provided form or web page."
This public records request is being made via email to your agency’s publicly posted public records request email address: publicrecordsrequest@vansd.org. This public records request will be honored and fulfilled by your agency via email as requested or relief will be sought per statute.

NATIVE ELECTRONIC FORMAT

Please provide all identified public records in their NATIVE electronic format. Unless the records exist IN PAPER FORM ONLY, DO NOT instead create new records by printing native stored electronic files, then scanning and re-printing these newly scanned prints only to reproduce them in again in electronic production.

FEES

In the event that there are fees, please inform us of the total charges in advance of fulfilling the request in strict compliance with all provisions of the Washington State Public Records Act.

EXEMPTION LOGS

Please ensure all redactions or exemptions claimed by your agency in the production of responsive records are accompanied by a complete and detailed exemption log noting the valid legal reason for each exemption at each redaction location in the record produced, as well as the specific number of pages if any that your agency redacts or withholds in their entirety. Each redaction should be noted by footnote or by a clear reference to the specific justification for that redaction, and only the minimal exempt portion of any record may be withheld.

COMMERICAL PURPOSE DECLARATION

The Washington State Public Records Act prohibits the disclosure of “lists of individuals” for a commercial purpose (RCW 42.56.070(8)). I declare this public records request is not being made for any commercial purpose whatsoever. Also, this public records request is not being made for a "list of individuals." This declaration satisfies all requirements of RCW 42.56 regarding prohibitions on lists and commercial purposes. No additional commercial purpose declaration will be completed for this public records request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. We look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

•	All complaints received by Minnesota Department of Labor and Industry between 1960 and 1993 originating from employees of the Great Northern Railroad, Burlington Northern Railroad or Burlington Northern Santa Fe Railroad and relating to work performed in the state of Minnesota.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

Sincerely,

Kevin LaMarca

title: Holocaust Survey (South Colonie Central School District)

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Holocaust Survey (South Colonie Central School District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

By way of background, on August 10, 2022, Governor Kathy Hochul signed into law Chapter 490 of the Laws of 2022 requiring a survey regarding instruction on the Holocaust within New York State public school districts. Through the survey, superintendents are required to attest that the district is teaching about the Holocaust appropriately as part of classroom instruction aligned with the NYS Social Studies Learning Standards and §801 of Education Law.

In October 2022, Deputy Commissioner Angelique Johnson-Dingle sent a memo to public school superintendents including a copy of that survey and instructions for accessing and submitting the survey via the SED Monitoring and Vendor Performance System in the NYSED Business Portal.

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request all of the Holocaust Instruction Survey responses submitted since August 10, 2022.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jackson Parker

communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Holocaust Survey (South Colonie Central School District)
communications.communication:
I am writing to appeal the denial of my request for access to records under the New York Freedom of Information Law (FOIL) that I submitted on 3/6/23. The response I received indicated that the requested records are too broad, that some requests ask the agency to create documents, and that the requested records may be produced by other New York State agencies. Additionally, the response stated that some of the requested records are interagency communications.

While I understand that other New York State agencies may have similar data, I believe that your agency is in the best position to provide the specific records I have requested. As I stated in my initial request, I am seeking access to all Holocaust Instruction Survey responses submitted since August 10, 2022. These records are critical to understanding how public school districts are implementing the NYS Social Studies Learning Standards and §801 of Education Law in relation to instruction on the Holocaust. Without these records, it is impossible to assess whether these standards are being met and whether the public is being adequately informed about this critical topic.

Furthermore, I believe that the requested records are not too broad, as they are narrowly focused on a specific survey and date range. As such, I do not believe that my request requires the creation of new records, as the requested records should already exist in your agency's possession.

I would like to request a written explanation of any exemptions or reasons for denial of access, as required under FOIL. I believe that any applicable exemptions should be narrowly construed in accordance with the law, and that the public interest in disclosure outweighs any privacy or confidentiality concerns that may exist.

Finally, I would like to emphasize the importance of transparency and accountability in government, and the critical role that FOIL plays in promoting these values. The requested records are essential to ensuring that the New York State Education Department is fulfilling its obligations under the law, and I believe that they should be made available to the public.

In light of the foregoing, I respectfully request that you reconsider your denial of my request for access to the requested records. If you require any additional information or clarification, please do not hesitate to contact me.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.
